# workflows_publish_to_pubsub.yaml

main:
  params: [topic, attributes]
  steps:
    - init:
        assign:
          - project: ${sys.get_env("GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT")}
    - publish:
        call: http.post
        args:
          url: ${"https://pubsub.googleapis.com/v1/projects/" + project + "/topics/" + topic + ":publish"}
          auth:
            type: OAuth2
          body:
            messages:
              - attributes: ${attributes}

==============================

# workflows_publish_to_pubsub.yaml

main:
  params: [topic, attributes]
  steps:
    - init:
        assign:
          - project: ${sys.get_env("GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT")}
    - publish:
        call: http.post
        args:
          url: ${"https://pubsub.googleapis.com/v1/projects/" + project + "/topics/" + topic + ":publish"}
          auth:
            type: OAuth2
          body:
            messages:
              - attributes: ${attributes}

=====================================

IAM Roles Required
1. Cloud Scheduler
Service Account (Scheduler SA)
Used in the scheduler job to invoke Pub/Sub or Workflows.

Required Roles:

roles/pubsub.publisher â†’ to publish to Pub/Sub topics

(Optional) roles/workflows.invoker â†’ if you trigger Workflows directly

2. Cloud Workflows
Service Account used by the workflow runtime

Required Roles:

roles/pubsub.publisher â†’ to publish to Pub/Sub (via HTTP)

roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator â†’ if impersonating another SA

(Optional) roles/datastore.user â†’ if calling a Cloud Function/Run that accesses Datastore

3. Pub/Sub Topics
The following identities need roles/pubsub.publisher or roles/pubsub.subscriber on topics:


Identity	Role(s)	Access
Scheduler SA	roles/pubsub.publisher	Publishes trigger messages
Workflow SA	roles/pubsub.publisher	Publishes programmatic triggers
Cloud Function SA	roles/pubsub.subscriber	Receives messages (if not using HTTP)
4. Go Program (Cloud Run or Cloud Function)
Service Account used to deploy and run the Go service

Required Roles:

roles/datastore.user â†’ read/write to Firestore in Datastore mode

roles/storage.objectViewer â†’ read GCS objects (CSV)

roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator â†’ (optional) if impersonating other SAs

roles/logging.logWriter â†’ emit logs to Cloud Logging

ðŸ” Example IAM Policy Binding (gcloud)
